100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 2, 1926, notable world events include the ongoing tensions in the Middle East, as British forces continue to manage unrest in Palestine. In the United States, the stock market shows signs of stabilization following the recent economic downturn. Additionally, the League of Nations remains embroiled in discussions over disarmament, with member nations grappling with the implications of global peace efforts.
